00:26:39,220 --> 00:26:44,640
说她给国王下了毒 想为她自己夺取王位
That she was bent on taking the throne by herself by poisoning the king.

176
00:26:48,150 --> 00:26:51,990
几周后 国王死了
A few weeks later the king died.

177
00:26:57,590 --> 00:27:01,090
而王子还年轻 不能登基为国王
The prince was too young to take the king's place...

178
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:07,180
因此根据法律 女王将统治一年
So, by law, the queen would rule for another year.

179
00:27:11,190 --> 00:27:13,860
未来已成未知
The future was uncertain.

180
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:30,140
期间 王子有了心上人
The prince meanwhile had given away his heart.

181
00:27:30,310 --> 00:27:34,650
她既漂亮又聪明 是一个农夫的独女
She was beautiful and smart, and though only a farmer's daughter...

182
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:38,030
全国都觉得他们很般配
the kingdom smiled on the match.

183
00:27:41,620 --> 00:27:45,880
然而 女王更享受当女王的乐趣
The queen however, was rather enjoying being queen.

184
00:27:46,050 --> 00:27:50,220
除了嫁给王子还有什么更好的办法保留王位呢
And what better way to remain so, than to marry the prince herself?

185
00:27:50,390 --> 00:27:52,390
什么 这真恶心
What? That's disgusting.

186
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:55,060
- 她是他外婆 - 是他继任的外婆
- She was his grandmother. - Step grandmother...

187
00:27:55,230 --> 00:27:58,820
但还是一个年轻 漂亮的女人 不要忘记这一点
and still a young, beautiful woman herself, don't forget.

188
00:27:58,990 --> 00:28:01,830
王子可不喜欢这主意
The prince, however, didn't like the idea.

189
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:10,840
他带着农夫的女儿 骑马逃至夜深
He took the farmer's daughter, and they rode away into the night.

190
00:28:13,770 --> 00:28:17,020
他们在紫杉树的树枝下停下休息
They stopped to rest under the branches of a yew tree.

191
00:28:17,190 --> 00:28:19,690
那是你
That's you.

192
00:28:19,860 --> 00:28:23,030
第二天早晨 王子醒来
The next morning the Prince awoke.

193
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:26,370
起来了 我的爱人 他说道
"Arise, my beloved" he said.

194
00:28:26,540 --> 00:28:30,300
但农夫的女儿一动也不动
But the farmer's daughter did not steer...

195
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:34,710
而王子注意到了血
Which was when the prince noticed the blood.

196
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:35,930
血?
Blood?

197
00:28:36,130 --> 00:28:38,310
有人在晚上杀了他的爱人
Someone had killed his beloved in the night.

198
00:28:38,310 --> 00:28:39,480
什么
What?

199
00:28:40,650 --> 00:28:42,820
女王 他哭泣道
"The Queen" he cried.

200
00:28:42,990 --> 00:28:46,490
女王杀了我的新娘
"The queen has murdered my bride."

201
00:28:46,660 --> 00:28:51,170
村民们满腔怒火 复仇心切 他们暴动了
The villagers, full of fury and vengeance, rose up at the crime.

202
00:28:51,330 --> 00:28:54,420
我就在那时走动了起来
It was then that I came walking.

203
00:29:17,940 --> 00:29:21,220
女王再也没有出现过
The queen was never seen again.

204
00:29:24,810 --> 00:29:26,650
很好 她罪有应得
Good. She deserved it.

205
00:29:27,570 --> 00:29:30,800
我外婆的事  我想你也帮不上忙
Now, I don't suppose you can help me with my grandma.

206
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:33,410
故事还没结束
The story is not yet finished.

207
00:29:34,170 --> 00:29:36,990
我把女王带到了非常远的地方
I took the queen and carried her far enough away

208
00:29:37,190 --> 00:29:40,070
人们永远不会再找到她
so that the townspeople would never find her...

209
00:29:40,190 --> 00:29:43,980
在海边的一个村庄里  她开始了新的生活
to a village by the sea, where she began a new life.

210
00:29:44,590 --> 00:29:46,390
但她杀了农夫的女儿
But she killed the farmer's daughter.

211
00:29:46,810 --> 00:29:49,050
你怎么能救一个杀人犯
How can you save a murderer?

212
00:29:49,940 --> 00:29:51,190
你真的是一个怪物
You really are a monster.

213
00:29:51,260 --> 00:29:53,820
我从没说是她杀了农夫的女儿
I never said she killed farmer's daughter.

214
00:29:54,070 --> 00:29:57,680
我只说过王子那么说的
I only said that the prince said it was so.

215
00:29:58,330 --> 00:30:01,130
那晚王子一直没入睡
The prince never fell asleep that night...

216
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:05,630
却等着农夫的女儿沉眠于睡梦中
but waited for the farmer's daughter to be lost in her dreams...

217
00:30:06,150 --> 00:30:09,100
然后展开了他真正的计划
and then began his real plan.

218
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:11,570
什么
What?

219
00:30:12,730 --> 00:30:17,990
他知道她的死会引发完全毁灭女王的星星之火
He knew her death would start a fire that would consume the queen entire.

220
00:30:22,750 --> 00:30:25,180
这是个糟糕的故事 是骗人的
That's a terrible story. And a cheat.

221
00:30:25,330 --> 00:30:26,930
这是一个真实的故事
It's a true story.

222
00:30:26,940 --> 00:30:29,650
很多真实的事物都像是骗人的
Many things that are true feel like a cheat.

223
00:30:29,970 --> 00:30:32,290
王国得到了值得拥有的王子
Kingdoms get their princes they deserve.

224
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:34,820
农夫的女儿死于无辜
Farmers' daughters die for no reason.

225
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:37,950
而有时候女巫又应该被救
And sometimes witches merit saving.

226
00:30:38,740 --> 00:30:41,570
你可能会惊讶 实际上 经常会这样
Quite often, actually. You'd be surprised.

227
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:48,890
所以好王子是一个杀人犯 而邪恶的女王到最后却不是女巫?
So the good prince was a murderer and the evil queen was no witch after all?

228
00:30:48,970 --> 00:30:52,730
女王当然是女巫
No, the queen was most certainly a witch...

229
00:30:52,890 --> 00:30:56,200
也可能制造更大的邪恶
and could well have been on her way to great evil.

230
00:30:56,310 --> 00:30:57,870
谁知道呢
Who can say?

231
00:30:57,950 --> 00:30:59,510
那你为什么要救她
Then why did you save her then?

232
00:30:59,570 --> 00:31:03,500
因为她不是凶手
Because what she was not, was a murderer.

233
00:31:05,580 --> 00:31:07,530
她没给国王下毒
She hadn't poisoned the king.

234
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:10,850
他只是年迈了
He had merely grown old.

235
00:31:12,090 --> 00:31:13,860
王子有被抓起来吗
Did the prince ever get caught?

236
00:31:14,030 --> 00:31:16,980
没有 他成了一个受人爱戴的国王
No. He became a much beloved king...

237
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:21,530
开心地统治着直到死去
who ruled happily until the end of his long days.

238
00:31:21,620 --> 00:31:23,080
没错
Oh yes.

239
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,010
我不明白
I don't get it.

240
00:31:25,660 --> 00:31:26,870
谁是好人呢
Who is the good guy here?

241
00:31:26,950 --> 00:31:29,880
不会一直有好人 康纳・奥马利...
There is not always a good guy, Conor O'Malley...

242
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:32,010
也不会一直有坏人
nor is there always a bad one.

243
00:31:32,030 --> 00:31:34,550
很多人都介于这两者之间
Most people are somewhere in between.

244
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:39,170
这些怎么从外婆那把我救出来
So how is this all meant to save me from grandma?

245
00:31:40,790 --> 00:31:44,050
不是从她那把你救出来
It is not her you need saving from.

246
00:32:03,990 --> 00:32:05,830
故事总有两面性
There are always two sides to a story.

247
00:32:05,990 --> 00:32:08,360
你们有多少人知道一句俗话
Now, how many of you know the saying:

248
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:13,950
棍棒和石头可能会打断我的骨头 但言词永远伤害不了我
"Stick and stones may break my bones, but words can never touch me?"

249
00:32:14,710 --> 00:32:17,430
这样的话 下次要有人对你们说了什么 只要记住...
That way the next time someone says something to you just remember...

250
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,570
很好 你到家了
Good, you're home.

251
00:32:45,600 --> 00:32:47,890
你妈妈在楼上 她想和你谈谈
Your mum's upstairs. She wants to talk to you.

252
00:32:47,930 --> 00:32:51,290
- 什么 - 你爸周日会坐飞机过来
- What? - Your father's flying in on Sunday.

253
00:32:51,820 --> 00:32:53,910
爸爸要来了? 从美国过来?
Dad's coming? From America?

254
00:32:54,610 --> 00:32:56,280
去吧
Go on.

255
00:32:56,450 --> 00:32:58,160
她等着呢
She's waiting.

256
00:32:58,330 --> 00:33:00,160
打包好你的东西
And pack your bag.

257
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:02,260
你要来和我住几天
You're coming to stay with me for a few days.

258
00:33:03,590 --> 00:33:05,680
去吧
Go on.

259
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:20,830
那棵树很赞
That tree is amazing.

260
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:24,370
在这里矗立了数千年
It's been here for thousands of years.

261
00:33:27,380 --> 00:33:28,550
你觉得怎么样
What do you think?

262
00:33:29,740 --> 00:33:32,410
我觉得外婆想把我变成蒂娜・特纳
I think Grandma is trying to turn me into Tina Turner.

263
00:33:34,030 --> 00:33:35,330
她一定是她粉丝
She must be a fan.

264
00:33:40,410 --> 00:33:42,280
我为什么要和外婆住
Why am I going to stay with grandma?

265
00:33:46,490 --> 00:33:48,060
你要回医院吗
Are you going back to the hospital?

266
00:33:49,470 --> 00:33:52,430
过来 康
Come here, Con.

267
00:33:56,770 --> 00:34:00,190
上一次治疗没达到效果
This latest treatment is not doing what it's supposed to.

268
00:34:01,860 --> 00:34:03,620
所以要调整下
So they're going to adjust it...

269
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:05,840
尝试别的
try something else.

270
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:10,390
-  就这样? - 就这样
- That's all? - That's all.

271
00:34:11,590 --> 00:34:13,110
你确定吗
Are you sure?

272
00:34:16,230 --> 00:34:17,770
确定
I'm sure.

273
00:34:19,370 --> 00:34:20,940
因为...
Because...

274
00:34:21,700 --> 00:34:23,320
你能跟我讲的
you can tell me, you know.

275
00:34:45,420 --> 00:34:47,280
一切都会好起来 康纳
Everything will be fine, Conor.

276
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:50,550
你会看到的
You'll see.

277
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:39,280
等等我们 康纳 你要去哪
Wait for us, Conor. Where are you going?

278
00:35:41,050 --> 00:35:43,080
- 不要碰他  - 不要碰他?
- Don't touch him. - "Don't touch him?"

279
00:35:43,170 --> 00:35:46,310
- 我给他脸上来一下怎么了 - 我说了别碰他
- With a punch to the face? - I said don't touch him.

280
00:35:48,350 --> 00:35:50,460
奥马利和我有共识
O'Malley and I have an understanding.

281
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:53,530
我是唯一能碰他的人
I'm the only one who touches him.

282
00:35:54,700 --> 00:35:55,970
对吗
Isn't that right?

283
00:35:56,950 --> 00:35:58,070
告诉我
Now tell me.

284
00:35:59,620 --> 00:36:04,140
为什么每次我转过身 你就在那看着我
Why is it that every time I turn around, you're there looking at me?

285
00:36:04,630 --> 00:36:08,270
你不觉得很怪吗
Getting a bit odd, don't you think?

286
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:13,030
抱歉 这有点残酷
Sorry, that was a bit harsh.

287
00:36:13,150 --> 00:36:15,120
今天 生活未能一路顺风
Life isn't really going your way today, are they?

288
00:36:15,980 --> 00:36:18,160
因为你选错了地方
You picked the wrong spot.

289
00:36:34,980 --> 00:36:36,640
我要带人去看房子
I have a house to show.

290
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:40,160
我相信你会一个人待在这里等你父亲
I trust you alone here till your father shows up.

291
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:42,180
我现在不是五岁
I'm not five years old.

292
00:36:44,170 --> 00:36:45,790
这是正确的时间
This is the correct time.

293
00:36:45,980 --> 00:36:49,160
你手机 电脑上都不对
Not the one on your phone or on the computer,

294
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:50,950
就连新闻上的也不对
not even on the news.

295
00:36:51,410 --> 00:36:54,410
这是我母亲的 你曾外婆的
That was my mother's, your great grandmother's.

296
00:36:54,490 --> 00:36:57,330
完美无误地走了一百多年
Perfect timekeeping for over a hundred years.

297
00:36:58,100 --> 00:37:00,330
康纳 过来收拾好
Conor! Pack up your rucksack.

298
00:37:02,350 --> 00:37:05,870
我不希望你父亲觉得我让你生活在猪圈里
I don't want your father to think that I'm keeping you in a pigsty.

299
00:37:06,370 --> 00:37:08,450
- 真是没什么机会 - 是的
- Not much shots of that. - No.

300
00:37:08,930 --> 00:37:11,450
等你去了医院
When you go to the hospital,

301
00:37:11,650 --> 00:37:14,210
你父亲可能不会注意到你母亲会有多累
your father may not notice how tired you mother's becoming.

302
00:37:14,210 --> 00:37:17,470
所以我们必须确保他不会待太久
So we have to make sure he does not overstay his welcome.

303
00:37:17,870 --> 00:37:20,180
这跟以前的事无关
Not that that's been a historically problem.

304
00:37:20,980 --> 00:37:23,890
不能吃鸡蛋 这周你已经吃过两次了
No eggs. You already had eggs twice this week.

305
00:37:24,180 --> 00:37:25,600
如果你饿了
If you are getting hungry,

306
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:28,260
冰箱里有菠菜你可以蒸
there is spinach in the fridge you can steam.

307
00:37:28,390 --> 00:37:30,330
当然
Yeah, sure.

308
00:37:30,500 --> 00:37:31,880
什么都别碰
Don't touch anything.

309
00:37:34,420 --> 00:37:37,890
我会尽最大努力什么都不碰的
I will do my very best not to.

310
00:38:12,060 --> 00:38:13,560
找到了
Get it.

311
00:39:46,900 --> 00:39:48,190
爸爸
Dad.

312
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:28,520
你怎么样 康 你看上去很累
How are you doing, Con? You look tired.

313
00:40:28,690 --> 00:40:29,810
我挺好
I'm fine.

314
00:40:29,980 --> 00:40:32,810
妈妈在用新药 会让她好转
Mum's on this new medicine. And it will make her better.

315
00:40:32,980 --> 00:40:35,860
她每两个星期去次医院
She goes to the hospital every two weeks...

316
00:40:36,020 --> 00:40:40,900
他们把药物打入她的血流
and they pump the medicine into her bloodstream.

317
00:40:41,060 --> 00:40:44,830
她会发病几天 然后好转
She's sick for the next few days, but she's better again.

318
00:40:51,810 --> 00:40:56,470
- 你妹妹最近挺好  - 同父异母的妹妹
- Your sister is doing better. - Half sister.

319
00:40:57,440 --> 00:40:58,600
是的
Yeah.

320
00:40:58,770 --> 00:41:00,690
我想让你和她见见
I'd still love you to meet her.

321
00:41:02,140 --> 00:41:05,190
我跟你外婆谈过了 想把你带去洛杉矶
I've been talking with your grandmother about bringing you out to LA.

322
00:41:06,060 --> 00:41:08,910
- 你想让我去洛杉矶? - 是的
- You want me to come to LA? - Yeah absolutely.

323
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:11,340
- 你想去的吧 - 是的
- You'd like that wouldn't you? - Yeah.

324
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,680
我们去那过圣诞
We were thinking over Christmas,

325
00:41:12,750 --> 00:41:14,670
回来正好能上学
that way you can be back here in time for school.

326
00:41:16,740 --> 00:41:18,500
你意思是去玩咯
So you mean just for a visit then?

327
00:41:18,700 --> 00:41:20,350
对啊 会很棒
Yeah, but it would be great.

328
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:23,180
我不想和外婆住
I don't want to live with grandma.

329
00:41:23,380 --> 00:41:26,050
那是个老女人的房子 里面全是老女人的东西
It's an old lady's house with old ladies' things.

330
00:41:26,110 --> 00:41:27,960
你什么都不能碰 哪里都不能坐
Can't touch anything or sit anywhere.

331
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:30,160
连胡闹两秒钟都不行
Can't even leave a mess for two seconds.

332
00:41:30,230 --> 00:41:31,230
康纳 我知道 但...
Conor, I know, but...

333
00:41:31,390 --> 00:41:34,410
我想要自己房子的房间 自己的东西
I want to have my own room in my my own house with my own things.

334
00:41:34,510 --> 00:41:35,790
你来美国住也不会有啊 康纳
Well, you wouldn't have that in America, Conor.

335
00:41:35,820 --> 00:41:37,350
几乎没足够的空间给我们三个人
There is barely enough room for the three of us.

336
00:41:37,350 --> 00:41:39,060
- 我不在乎  - 康纳 听着...
- I do not care. - Conor listen...

337
00:41:39,060 --> 00:41:41,360
- 她太严厉了 - 你的家人 你的生活 你的朋友...
- She's so strict. - Your family, your life, your friends...

338
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:45,230
- 她家像个博物馆 - 你的学校 一切都在这里 好吗
- Her house is like a museum. - Your school, all of it is here, okay?

339
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:47,080
把你带离这里是不公平的
It would be unfair to take you out of here.

340
00:41:47,230 --> 00:41:48,570
- 对谁不公平 - 康纳
- Unfair to whom? - Conor.

341
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:03,480
你外婆好像还没回家
Doesn't look like your grandmother's home yet.

342
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:07,640
她有时会在我睡觉后再回医院去
She sometimes goes back to the hospital after I go to bed.

343
00:42:07,810 --> 00:42:10,310
护士让她睡在一张椅子上
The nurses let her sleep in a chair.

344
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:13,180
你外婆不喜欢我
Hey, just because your grandmother

345
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:14,630
不代表她是个坏人
doesn't like me, doesn't make her a bad person.

346
00:42:14,630 --> 00:42:16,400
她说你总有始无终
She says you're all start and no finish.

347
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:21,900
她有权表达她自己的看法
Well, she entitled to her own opinion.

348
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:25,230
你会待多久
How long are you here for?

